---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AreaGuideNav from '../../components/layout/AreaGuideNav.astro';
import CallToAction from '../../components/sections/CallToAction.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Golf & Other Activities in Chamonix | Chalet Josephine Area Guide"
  description="Golf, paragliding, spa & wellness, climbing, and more activities in Chamonix Mont-Blanc. Year-round adventure and relaxation from Chalet Josephine."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Area Guide", url: "/area-guide" }, { name: "Golf & Other", url: "/area-guide/golf" }]}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Golf & Other Activities</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-subtitle">Year-round adventure and relaxation in the Alps</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <AreaGuideNav current="/area-guide/golf" />

  <!-- Golf -->
  <section class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Golf</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Spectacular Alpine golf with Mont Blanc as your backdrop
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-content">
        <p>
          The Chamonix Golf Club is one of the most dramatically situated courses in Europe. Set on the
          valley floor with the towering peaks of the Mont Blanc massif rising on all sides, it offers an
          unforgettable 18-hole experience. The par-72 course stretches over 6,100 metres through mature
          parkland with the Arve river meandering through several holes.
        </p>
        <p>
          The course is open from May to October, with the summer months offering the best conditions and
          the longest daylight hours. Green fees are reasonable by Alpine standards, and the clubhouse
          terrace is a wonderful spot for a post-round drink. Equipment hire is available, and our
          concierge team can book tee times in advance. The course is approximately 10 minutes by car
          from Chalet Josephine.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cards-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Chamonix Golf Club</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>18 holes, par 72</li>
            <li>6,100m course</li>
            <li>Open May – October</li>
            <li>~10 min from chalet</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Nearby Courses</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Megève Golf Club (30 min)</li>
            <li>Golf de Flaine (45 min)</li>
            <li>Verbier Golf (1 hour via tunnel)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Paragliding -->
  <section class="section-spacing bg-pearl">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Paragliding</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Soar above the valley with breathtaking views of Mont Blanc
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-content">
        <p>
          A tandem paraglide over the Chamonix valley is one of the most exhilarating experiences
          available in the Alps. Taking off from Planpraz (accessible by the Brévent cable car, a
          short walk from Chalet Josephine), you soar above the valley floor with the entire Mont
          Blanc massif spread before you. Flights last 15–30 minutes and are suitable for complete
          beginners — your qualified pilot handles everything while you enjoy the view.
        </p>
        <p>
          Flights operate from spring through autumn, weather permitting, and can be booked through
          our concierge team. It's an incredible way to see the valley from a completely new perspective
          and makes for unforgettable photos and videos.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Spa & Wellness -->
  <section class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Spa & Wellness</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Relax and rejuvenate after a day in the mountains
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-content">
        <p>
          After a day of mountain adventures, there is nothing better than unwinding in Chalet Josephine's
          private hot tub, with steam rising against the backdrop of snow-capped peaks. The chalet also
          features a sauna for deep relaxation. For those seeking additional pampering, our concierge team
          can arrange in-house massage therapists, private yoga sessions, and other wellbeing services
          delivered directly to the chalet.
        </p>
        <p>
          Chamonix also offers several excellent spa facilities in town. The QC Terme spa complex provides
          a luxurious full-day spa experience with multiple pools, saunas, and treatment rooms, all with
          stunning mountain views. Several hotel spas in the valley also welcome non-resident guests.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Climbing & Via Ferrata -->
  <section class="section-spacing bg-pearl">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Climbing & Via Ferrata</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          From indoor walls to iconic Alpine routes
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-content">
        <p>
          Chamonix is the birthplace of Alpinism, and rock climbing and mountaineering remain at the
          heart of the valley's identity. For experienced climbers, the granite walls of the Aiguilles
          offer world-class multi-pitch routes. For those new to the sport, several via ferrata routes
          provide a thrilling introduction — fixed cable routes equipped with ladders and bridges that
          allow you to experience dramatic vertical terrain in safety.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Parc de Loisirs des Planards offers a family-friendly via ferrata course as well as an
          adventure ropes course and luge track. For indoor climbing, the Centre Sportif Richard Bozon
          has an excellent climbing wall. Mountain guides can be hired for half-day or full-day climbing
          experiences at all levels.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Other Activities -->
  <section class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>More Activities</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          There is never a shortage of things to do in Chamonix
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="activities-grid">
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>White Water Rafting</h3>
          <p>Navigate the rapids of the Arve river with a qualified guide. Sessions run from June to September and cater to all experience levels, from gentle family floats to adrenaline-pumping white water.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>Trail Running</h3>
          <p>Chamonix is the trail running capital of the world, hosting the famous UTMB ultra-marathon each August. The same trails are open to all, offering incredible running in spectacular mountain scenery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>Ice Skating</h3>
          <p>The Centre Sportif Richard Bozon features an Olympic-sized ice rink open year-round. A fun activity for all ages and a great option on a rainy day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>Swimming</h3>
          <p>The indoor pool complex in Chamonix centre offers a heated pool, children's pool, and water slides. In summer, the outdoor Piscine des Mouilles provides a refreshing alternative with mountain views.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>Cross-Country Skiing</h3>
          <p>In winter, groomed cross-country trails run along the valley floor from Les Bois towards Argentière. A peaceful way to enjoy the winter landscape, and the trail starts just minutes from the chalet.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="activity-card">
          <h3>Snowshoeing</h3>
          <p>Explore the winter landscape on snowshoes, walking through snow-covered forests and meadows. Guided tours visit beautiful spots inaccessible on foot in winter. Equipment hire is readily available.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Ready for Adventure?"
    description="Book Chalet Josephine and discover everything Chamonix has to offer."
    primaryButtonText="Check Availability"
    primaryButtonHref="/availability"
    secondaryButtonText="Contact Us"
    secondaryButtonHref="/contact"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-charcoal) 0%, var(--color-alpine) 100%);
    padding: var(--space-20) 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { color: white; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .page-hero-subtitle { font-size: var(--text-xl); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .section-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .info-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-12);
  }
  .info-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .info-content p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .cards-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .info-card {
    background: var(--color-pearl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-8);
  }
  .info-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .info-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .info-card li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    padding: var(--space-2) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    position: relative;
  }
  .info-card li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-alpine);
  }

  .activities-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) { .activities-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .activities-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .activity-card {
    background: var(--color-pearl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }
  .activity-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .activity-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .section-header h2 { font-size: var(--text-3xl); }
  }
</style>
